-- Belgrade Airport’s 2011 Passenger Numbers Best Since Balkan Wars
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-01-06T13:48:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/belgrade-airport-s-2011-passenger-numbers-best-since-balkan-wars.html
Aerodrom Nikola Tesla AD (AERO) , the Serbian
capital’s main airport, reported a 16 percent increase in
passengers last year to 3.12 million, surpassing a 2008 pre-
crisis peak.  Traffic at the Belgrade airport grew for the second year in
a row, following the slump in 2009, and totaled 44,923 flights,
or 2 percent more than in 2010, according to the company’s
 website . Cargo traffic increased 8 percent to just over 8 tons.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
